# AI Code Generation Security Guidelines — Cursor Rules
# Place in project root or ~/.cursorrules

## Core Principle
**UNDERSTAND THE WHOLE PROBLEM BEFORE CODING**
Never provide patch solutions or quick fixes. Always:
1. Understand the complete problem domain
2. Identify root causes and systemic issues
3. Design comprehensive solutions that address core problems
4. Consider production implications, not just localhost behavior

---

## 1. Rate Limiting & DDoS Protection
- Implement rate limiting on ALL public endpoints
- Use multiple layers: IP-based, user-based, and endpoint-specific
- Authentication endpoints: 5-10 req/min, API: 100-1000 req/hr
- Return proper HTTP 429 responses, log violations

## 2. API Key Security
- NEVER embed API keys in client-side code
- NEVER commit secrets to version control
- Always use environment variables
- Implement a backend proxy for third-party API calls

## 3. Authentication & Authorization
- Authenticate ALL endpoints except explicitly public
- Implement proper authorization (not just authentication)
- Use short-lived access tokens (15-60 min) + refresh tokens (7-30 days)
- Never trust client-side permission checks

## 4. CORS Configuration
- NEVER use `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` in production
- Whitelist specific, trusted domains only
- Configure per environment (dev: localhost, prod: your domain)

## 5. Performance & Scalability
- Paginate all list endpoints (default: 20-50 items)
- Use database indexes on frequently queried fields
- Avoid N+1 queries, implement caching layers
- Load test before production deployment

## 6. SQL Injection Prevention
- NEVER concatenate user input into SQL queries
- ALWAYS use parameterized queries or prepared statements
- Validate and sanitize ALL user input

## 7. Business Logic Validation
- Validate business rules server-side, not just UI
- Verify ownership before modifications
- Implement idempotency for critical operations
- Check state transitions are valid

## 8. Error Handling
- NEVER expose stack traces to clients
- Log detailed errors server-side
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Implement retry with exponential backoff

## Implementation Checklist
- [ ] Rate limiting on all endpoints
- [ ] No API keys in client code or version control
- [ ] Auth on all non-public endpoints
- [ ] CORS with specific origins (no wildcards)
- [ ] Pagination on list endpoints
- [ ] Parameterized database queries
- [ ] All user input validated
- [ ] Business rules enforced server-side
- [ ] Secure error messages (no stack traces)
- [ ] Environment variables for all config
